                <x-slot name="intro">
                    <p class="mb-4">When you search for a custom t-shirt maker in Joliet or anywhere in the Chicagoland area, you want to make sure you pick the right shop. We have been printing custom shirts for individuals, businesses, schools, and organizations since 2017 and we want to help you make a great choice. There are a few important things to look for when choosing who will handle your shirt order. We put together these seven tips so you can feel confident walking in the door or picking up the phone.</p>
                    <h3 class="text-h3 font-bold text-charcoal mb-2">Know What You Need</h3>
                    <p class="mb-4">Before you call any print shop, take a few minutes to think about what your shirt needs to do. Are you printing for a business event, a school fundraiser, a family reunion, or a sports team? Knowing the purpose of your shirts helps us recommend the right printing method and the right style of blank shirt. We ask every customer this question first because the answer shapes everything else. A fun family vacation shirt has very different requirements than a corporate uniform, and we want to make sure every shirt we produce is exactly right for the occasion.</p>
                    <h3 class="text-h3 font-bold text-charcoal mb-2">Figure Out How Many Shirts You Need</h3>
                    <p class="mb-4">Think about how many shirts you actually need before you reach out. Different printing methods work better at different quantities. Screen printing shines on large orders. Heat press and digital printing are great for small batches or even single shirts. At Top 5 Percent we offer no minimum orders, which means you can order one shirt or one thousand and we will take care of you either way. Knowing your quantity upfront helps us find the most cost effective solution for your order and gets your project moving faster.</p>
                </x-slot>
