                    <h3 class="text-h3 font-bold text-charcoal mb-2">Look for Strong Design and Graphic Capability</h3>
                    <p class="mb-4">A good custom shirt printer should have strong design skills in house. You should not have to go somewhere else to get your design ready. We have experienced graphic designers on staff who can build your idea from scratch or take your existing logo and prepare it for print. If you have something in mind but are not sure how to describe it, we can help you figure it out. We work with customers all across Will County including Joliet, Shorewood, Plainfield, and Lockport to bring their creative vision to life on fabric. Great design is the foundation of a great shirt, and we take that seriously on every single order we take on.</p>
                    <h3 class="text-h3 font-bold text-charcoal mb-2">Ask About Turnaround Time</h3>
                    <p class="mb-4">Rush orders are sometimes unavoidable. Ask the print shop how quickly they can get your shirts done and whether they have same day or next day options available. We offer same day service on select orders so if your event snuck up on you, we can often still save the day. We plan production carefully so we can give you an honest turnaround time from the very beginning and stick to it. No surprises and no excuses. When you need shirts on a tight deadline in Joliet, Romeoville, or anywhere in the Chicagoland area, we are the shop to call.</p>
